1. Definitions

   "Software" means the source code, documentation, configuration, and other files
   distributed under this license in this repository.

   "You" means any individual or legal entity exercising permissions granted here.

   "Attribution" means keeping all copyright and license notices in the Software,
   and in every public distribution, documentation page, UI, or marketing material
   that features the Software or a Derivative, a prominent notice equivalent to:

       Uses code from SkyLaTry Hermes plugins
       https://github.com/SkyLaTry/<repository-name>
       Copyright (c) SkyLaTry — licensed under the SkyLaTry Shared Source License

   "Derivative" means any modified version, fork, merged work, plugin, service,
   or product that is based on or incorporates any part of the Software.

   "Commercial Use" means use of the Software or a Derivative in connection with
   a product, service, or activity that generates or is intended to generate
   revenue, fees, donations tied to the offering, advertising revenue, or other
   commercial advantage.

   "Attributable Revenue" means gross revenue in a calendar year from products,
   services, subscriptions, support, or offerings whose value materially depends
   on the Software or a Derivative. Exclude unrelated revenue that would exist
   without the Software.

   "Revenue Threshold" means USD 25,000 of Attributable Revenue in a calendar year.

   "Revenue Share Rate" means ten percent (10%) of Attributable Revenue above the
   Revenue Threshold in that calendar year.

2. Grant for non-commercial use

   Subject to Sections 3–8, SkyLaTry grants You a royalty-free, worldwide,
   non-exclusive license to use, copy, modify, and distribute the Software and
   Derivatives for non-commercial purposes only.

3. Attribution (required for all use)

   You must provide Attribution for any use, copy, modification, public display,
   or distribution of the Software or a Derivative, whether commercial or
   non-commercial.

4. Commercial use

   4.1 Below the Revenue Threshold
       Commercial Use is permitted only if You comply with Section 3 (Attribution)
       and You do not misrepresent origin or authorship.

   4.2 At or above the Revenue Threshold
       If Your Attributable Revenue in a calendar year meets or exceeds the
       Revenue Threshold, You must, in addition to Attribution:

       (a) notify SkyLaTry at the contact address in LICENSING.md within 30 days
           of crossing the threshold;
       (b) pay the Revenue Share Rate on Attributable Revenue above the Revenue
           Threshold for that calendar year;
       (c) provide reasonable written reporting of Attributable Revenue upon
           request, no more than once per calendar quarter.

       Until payment and reporting obligations for the applicable period are met,
       Your commercial rights under this license are suspended for that period.

   4.3 Alternative commercial license
       SkyLaTry may offer a separate written commercial license with different
       terms. Contact details are in LICENSING.md.

5. Restrictions

   You may not:
   (a) remove or obscure copyright or license notices;
   (b) sublicense the Software under terms that remove Attribution or revenue-
